     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 " in 72hrs rescues a sub-24" base to 0.2).                    \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  160 +\cf13                                                               \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  161 +\cf13 3. **Piecewise linear interpolation.** Rather than hard step f\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 unctions between breakpoints, scores interpolate continuously \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 within each band. This avoids discontinuous jumps (e.g., a res\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 ort at 35" scoring identically to one at 30").                \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  162 +\cf13                                                               \cf3 \cb1 \
