     \cf15 \cb16  170 +\cf13 **Snow depth \'97 no hard exclude:**                             \cf3 \cb1        \
     \cf15 \cb16  171 +\cf13 The original design hard-excluded resorts with < 24" base dept\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 h (score = 0.0). This was removed after live API testing showe\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 d Vail returning 0" in late March \'97 accurate at base elevation\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 , but the resort was still operating. Two concerns were confla\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 ted: (1) *is the resort open?* and (2) *how good are condition\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 s?* These are now separated: resort operating status is checke\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 d via `season_open`/`season_close` dates in the CSV (feasibili\cf3 \cb1 \
